cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with hyperspectral imaging and uses deep learning techniques for classification and segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses feature selection and uses iterative methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques implies that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with data-driven methods, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
